    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-04-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="66"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1897</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1429.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    2696, of February 25 last, transmitting the reply of the Tsung-li Yamên to the
                    measures suggested by this Department in its No. 1368 of November 25 last, for
                    the prevention of antiforeign riots.</p>
                <p>Before giving its views on the position taken by the Chinese Government on this
                    important subject, the Department will await your report of the conference which
                    your dispatch states it is your intention to have with the Yamên.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
